50|$|In the 1980s, <b>Hungarians</b> {{were the}} largest {{enumerated}} minority ethnic group. In 1989 approximately 560,000 <b>Hungarians</b> (concentrated in southern Slovakia) made up 11% of Slovakia's population. Despite significant anti-Hungarian sentiment in Slovakia, the postwar exchange of Slovaks in Hungary for <b>Hungarians</b> in Slovakia met with only limited success; {{the proportion of}} <b>Hungarians</b> in the population has changed little since 1930 (see History).|$|R
