5|$|Brand's {{involvement}} in smuggling Jews into Hungary began in July 1941, when Hansi Brand's sister and brother-in-law were {{caught up in}} the Kamianets-Podilskyi deportations. The <b>Hungarian</b> government sent 18,000 Jews to German-occupied Ukraine because they were unable to prove they were <b>Hungarian</b> citizens; 14,000–16,000 of them were shot by the SS. Brand paid a <b>Hungarian</b> counter-espionage officer to bring his wife's relatives back safely.|$|E
